NTT DATA Services strives to hire exceptional, innovative and passionate individuals who want to grow with us. If you want to be part of an inclusive, adaptable, and forward-thinking organization, apply now.  



We are currently seeking a Digital Engineering Lead Engineer to join our team in Hyderabad, Telangana (IN-TG), India (IN).  



Roles & Responsibilities:  

* The Automation Developer has strong technical skills, is detail-oriented, and has excellent problem-solving skills.
* Reviewing Microsoft Power Apps/Power Automate's best practices guidelines and support policies with the customer, including service levels and escalation procedures
* Experience with design and development of plugins, custom workflows, power apps, Power Automate, Azure functions, Logic Apps
* Maintain RPA and monitor the successful execution of automation product;
* Develop; configure programs, scripts and objects that are efficient, well structured, maintainable & easy to understand;
* Work collaboratively with operational and technical teams to deliver projects by assigned deadlines;
* Ability to understand a business process from a Process Definition Document (PDD) and to conceptualize it as an automated solution;
* Identify and communicate the technical infrastructure with standard Automation Anywhere design principles and conventions.
* Integration and deployment of RPA projects; ability to analyze business processes and recommend improvements and develop RPA solutions around them;
* Willingness and ability to blend business analysis with hands-on configuration of automated processes;
* Analyze, understand and document infrastructure requirements;
* Design the RPA process solutions in accordance the business processes in detail where required;
* Configure new RPA processes and objects using core workflow principles that are efficient, well structured, maintainable and easy to understand;
* Facilitating weekly summary status reports; monthly or quarterly support reviews and detailed review of root cause analysis findings when applicable Weekly cadence calls with the customer to track on-going support activities and projects
* Create and maintain solution documentation;



Basic Qualifications:  

* Bachelor's degree in business or related field
* 5+ years of development experience on Microsoft Power Apps / Power Automate
* Having any RPA development experience (Automation Anywhere / Blue Prism) is a plus



Preferences:  

* Experience working with development teams preferred
* Experience in systems implementation, business analysis



**About NTT DATA Services**  



NTT DATA Services is a recognized leader in IT and business services, including cloud, data and applications, headquartered in Texas. As part of NTT DATA, a $30 billion trusted global innovator with a combined global reach of over 80 countries, we help clients transform through business and technology consulting, industry and digital solutions, applications development and management, managed edge-to-cloud infrastructure services, BPO, systems integration and global data centers. We are committed to our clients' long-term success. Visit nttdata.com or LinkedIn to learn more.  



